						               													<description>Galactic Bounty Hunt (GBH) is a gateway board game where each player controls one of six different Bounty Hunters that are taking part in the Great Hunt &amp;ndash; the ultimate bounty hunting competition, which will determine who&amp;rsquo;ll earn the position of Leader of the Galactic Bounty Hunter&amp;rsquo;s Guild. Competitors will have to travel across the Galaxy, capturing dangerous creatures (and earning credits in the process) in different systems before being able to return to the Guild&amp;rsquo;s HQ and claiming the title of Leader. Equip your character with the best gear available and be on the lookout, for monsters might not be your deadliest foes &amp;ndash; other Bounty Hunters might not want to let you earn the so-coveted prize of the Great Hunt! Good hunting!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Features:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     GBH introduces players to many different gameplay mechanics and systems, in an easy to learn way &amp;ndash; the perfect introduction to the world of modern board games. Mechanics include dice rolls, card drawing, luck mitigation systems (ammo, equipments,etc), PvP (player-vs-player) combat and more.&amp;#10;     No player elimination and no Kingmaker effect: even when the game seems lost, players can still turn the tide in their favor.&amp;#10;     Beautiful cel-shaded, comic-style art.&amp;#10;     Six different Bounty Hunters to play as, each from a different species and System.&amp;#10;     Twelve different kinds of monsters to capture, two of each element.&amp;#10;     Dozens of different pieces of equipment, from weapon mods to consumable items, will give you an edge, as long as you choose carefully &amp;ndash; and can afford them.&amp;#10;     Warp through the Galaxy at light speed using the portals on each System &amp;ndash; but take heed, for you can&amp;rsquo;t be sure where each portal might take you.&amp;#10;     Fortune cards will keep the game unpredictable: they can help or hinder any of the players, independently of who triggered the event. Mix things up a little to turn the tide &amp;ndash; for or against you.&amp;#10;     Keep the best monsters you capture as pets to engage in fights with other players.&amp;#10;     Falling behind on your trophy collecting? Not to worry! Board another Hunter&amp;rsquo;s ship, engage in combat and try to steal one of their trophies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
